value.value: Ventral part of the insect trunk ectoderm.

The sum of all the structures in the embryo that will develop into the embryonic/larval tracheal system. This corresponds to the tracheal primordia and their component tracheal branch primordia along with primordia of the spiracles.
Visual organ of the larva. It consists of a dense cluster of 12 ciliated photoreceptor neurons.
Primordium of the insect embryo that gives rise to the larval Bolwig organ.
A bristle-like, non-innervated outgrowth of the arista. Each lateral is formed from the outgrowth of a single polyploid central core cell.
The developing adult after pupal-adult apolysis, i.e. from stage P8 (when yellow eye color first becomes visible through the pupal case), to eclosion.
Region of the dorsal mesothoracic disc that will develop into the mesothoracic tergum.

label.value: insect metatarsus of male prothoracic leg

value.value: First tarsal segment of the male prothoracic leg. In contrast to females, it has a sex comb, central bristle and 5 to 6 transverse rows of bristles (TR).
The region of the ectoderm posterior to the cephalic furrow.
An insect embryonic structure that develops from the dorsal ectoderm.

label.value: insect centro-posterior medial synaptic neuropil domain

value.value: A synaptic neuropil domain of the larval brain located posterior to the medial lobe of the mushroom body. It is separated from the centro-lateral compartment by the peduncle, and from the centro-posterior intermediate compartment by the antenno-cerebral tract to which it is connected via a branch.
The sum of all the developing presumptive components of a specific embryonic/larval system in an embryo.
Protocerebrum of the adult brain.
Any appendage segment that is part of some antenna.
Any appendage segment that is part of some leg.
Sensillum which is embedded in the body wall and has a specific cuticular structure involved in the transduction of some sensory signal as a part.

Sensillum with innervated external cuticular sensory structure consisting of one or more bipolar sensory neurons, and 3 support cells: a trichogen cell which makes the external cuticular sensory structure, a thecogen cell which makes the socket that holds the base of the external sensory structure and a tormogen cell which makes the cuticular matrix (cap) at the tip of the innervating dendrite(s).
Sensillum that is internal to the animal - i.e. having no part that is part of the cuticle.
Any sensillum (UBERON:6007152) that is part of some larva (UBERON:6001727).
Any sensillum (UBERON:6007152) that is part of some larval head (UBERON:6001730).
Specialized structure of the chorion of the egg.
Any sense organ (UBERON:6005155) that is part of some larval head (UBERON:6001730).
A region of cuticle and its underlying epidermis.
A segmental subdivision of the integument of the whole animal.

label.value: insect segmental subdivision of organ system

value.value: The part of some organism that is part of some specified segment.
Sense organ that is internal to the animal - i.e. having no part that is part of the cuticle.
A region of an epithelium that folds inwards from the epithelial plane to form a furrow.
A primordium of the insect embryo that gives rise to the larval abdominal histoblast nests.
A population of cells of the insect epidermis primordium that give rises to the abdominal histoblast primordium.
An insect embryonic structure that develops from the anterior ectoderm.
An insect embryonic structure that develops from the ventral ectoderm.
An insect embryonic structure that develops from the trunk mesoderm.
An insect embryonic structure that develops from the visceral mesoderm.
The sum of all the anlagen and primordia that will develop into a single system.
The part of the neuropil consisting largely of synapsing neuron projections.

Region of synaptic neuropil whose boundaries are largely discontinuities in the density of presynaptic terminals: high density in the synaptic neuropil domain, lower or zero density outside this region. These boundaries often correspond to a boundary with glial sheath, tract neuropil or cortex.
A closely associated group of synaptic neuropil domains.
A row of sensilla.

The pre-oral neuropils of the adult brain located above, around and partially below the esophagus, including the optic lobes. It excludes the gnathal ganglion. Developmentally, it comprises three fused neuromeres: protocerebrum, deutocerebrum, and tritocerebrum.
Region of the prothoracic leg disc that will develop into the prothoracic metatarsus.
Region of the antennal disc that will develop into the arista.
